THE Vice-President, Dr Philip Mpango is expected to grace the official opening of the trade and government institutions exhibition at the end of the week in Zanzibar. The trade and government institutions exhibition is part of activities to celebrate the 58th anniversary of the Union between Zanzibar and Tanganyika. It will be held at Maisara grounds. “Preparations for the celebration have been going on well. We are now in the final touches for the union celebrations to be marked at National level in Dodoma City on April 26th this year,” the State Minister- Office of the Second Vice-President of Zanzibar, Hamza Hassan Juma told a press conference. He said that the exhibition starts on April 22nd to May 6th this year, where Union government institutions operating in Zanzibar will display their services. Mr Juma said the exhibition has been organised by the Second Vice-President's Office in collaboration with the Zanzibar National Chamber of Commerce (ZNCC). He said it would be an opportunity for the people here to learn about institutions operating in the Isles under the Union government. “The 58th anniversary of the Union will also have a public forum tomorrow in Unguja, where the Isles Second Vice-President Hemed Suleiman Abdulla, is scheduled to give an opening speech. The minister mentioned among the benefits of the Union as the freedom of movement and land use in any part of the country. “We want all Tanzanians, particularly those born after the Union to understand the benefits of the political marriage initiated by founder leaders late Abeid Amani Karume and late Mwalimu Julius Nyerere,” the minister said. Secretary of the 58th anniversary celebrations organising committee, Mr Tahir Mussa encouraged people to attend both the forum and the exhibition.